<h1>Banned and Suspect Sites</h1>

<p>This screen lets you configure banned and suspect sites.  Banned sites are prohibited from logging in.  Suspect sites will cause an alert if a new character is created from that site.  For more help see <a href="https://aresmush.com/tutorials/config/sites">Configuring Banned/Suspect Sites</a>.</p>

<form method="POST" action="/admin/config_sites/update">


<div class="panel panel-primary">
    <div class="panel-heading">
        Suspect Sites
    </div>
    
    <div class="panel-body">
        <p>List suspect site host names or IP addresses, one per line.</p>
        
        <textarea name="suspect_sites" rows="10"><%= @sites['suspect'].join("\n") %></textarea>
        
    </div>
</div>

<div class="panel panel-primary">
    <div class="panel-heading">
        Banned Sites
    </div>
    
    <div class="panel-body">
        <p>List banned site host names or IP addresses, one per line.</p>
        
        <textarea name="banned_sites" rows="10"><%= @sites['banned'].join("\n") %></textarea>
        
    </div>
</div>


<div class="panel panel-primary">
    <div class="panel-heading">
        Ban Proxy Sites
    </div>
    
    <div class="panel-body">
        <p>This will ban known proxy sites.</p>
        
        <div class="alert alert-warning">This is not a magic bullet.  Proxy sites change frequently, and there are thousands out there.  It may also impact players who are legitimately using VPNs.  Consider it a last resort.</div>
        
              <input type="checkbox" name="ban_proxies" value="true"
              <% if @sites['ban_proxies'] %> checked <% end %>> Ban Proxy Sites
              </input>        
    </div>
</div>


<p>
<a href="/admin"><button type="button" class="btn btn-default">Cancel</button></a>
<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
</p>
</form>